  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nAfter opening the app, I had a group chat active. It fetched messages normally, I could see notifications going in the AC from the community, but the community didn't have the unread badge (blue dot or the red one in this case)\r\n\r\nEven when I opened the community, I couldn't see which channels had new messages, because the channel didn't become bold.\r\n\r\nHowever, new messages coming live from the `new.message` signal  did trigger the badge and the channel blodness.\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Have the app closed from account 1 which a group or public chat last active\r\n2. Using account 2, send messages to a channel in a community account 1 has access to\r\n3. Open account 1\r\n4. Wait for store nodes to give you the messages\r\n\r\nResult: see that there is no badge on the community and the channels and not bold\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe community has the unread badge and the channels with unread messages are bold\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version: 0.9.0RC1\r\n\r\n",
